<DOC><DOCNO> AP881018-0122 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-18-88 1412EDT</FILEID><FIRST>u i BC-Hurricane-Colombia     10-18 0159</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Hurricane-Colombia,0163</SECOND><HEAD>URGENT</HEAD><HEAD>50 Reported Dead Or Missing In Flooding Caused By Hurricane Joan</HEAD><DATELINE>BOGOTA, Colombia (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Flooding caused by Hurricane Joan leftabout 50 people dead or missing in a northern town in Colombia, anofficial with the state of Bolivar said Tuesday.   Water roared down three gullies in the town of Carmen de Bolivaron Monday as the hurricane passed over northern Colombia, theadministrative assistant for the state government, Victor LeonMendoza, said in a broadcast interview.   Carmen de Bolivar is 360 miles north of the capital of Bogota.   ``Preliminary reports from the mayor's office indicate thatabout 50 persons are dead or missing'' in the town, Leon Mendozatold the Colombian radio chain RCN.   The weather service said the storm buffeted northern Colombiawith heavy rain and winds of about 65 mph on Monday before headingnorthwest into the Caribbean toward the island of San Andres andthe coast of Nicaragua and Honduras.</TEXT></DOC>